        "body": "## Summary\n- add `minimax-cn` / `minimaxi` model support for the agent across CLI, core config, and the Mac settings UI\n- wire `MINIMAX_CN_API_KEY` with fallback to `MINIMAX_API_KEY` for explicit China endpoint use\n- bump Tachikoma to include the MiniMax China provider endpoint support\n- update provider docs and changelog; thanks @LLuke for reporting\n\nFixes #161\n\n## Proof\n- `pnpm run format`\n- `swift test --package-path Apps/CLI --filter 'AgentCommandModelParsingTests'`\n- `swift test --package-path Core/PeekabooCore --filter 'AIProviderParserTests|PeekabooAIServiceProviderTests|PeekabooAgentServiceTests'`\n- `pnpm run lint`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `pnpm run test:safe`\n- `/Users/steipete/Projects/agent-scripts/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n\nAutoreview: clean. One out-of-scope Tachikoma parser finding was rejected after source verification: the MiniMax CN qualified parser returns the optional directly, so invalid CN model strings return nil before OpenRouter fallback. Peekaboo also has regression coverage for CLI/config routing.\n",
